<section class="about" id="about">
<div class="container">
<h1>About Harry and Hermione</h1><hr />
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-8 ">

              <p class="body-text">
              <u>Harry and Hermione</u> is a non-for-profit, fan-created website.<br><br>
              <u>The original objective</u>: To create a website which replaces the void Portkey.org left behind as a website for fanfiction and forum for discussion based solely on the Harry/Hermione pairing.<br><br>
              <a href="/fanfiction">Fanfiction</a>: Was to be a place where authors could post their HHR stories.<br><br>
              The stories would be sorted by readers using a search function similar to what porkey and the archive have (by genres, pairings, rating, and length, options such as including "favorites" are also a possibility).<br><br>
              <a href="/fanart">Fanart</a>: A section called the “Gallery” would be dedicated to posting fan art and where artists can receive comments for their work<br><br>
              <u>Forum</u>: As the spiritual successor of the portkey website, we would also try to emulate the forum and its subsections within our own forum.
              The forum is designed for a variety of discussion that can be had under different topics: a general welcome section with FAQ, announcements,
              and introduction, a shipping subsection where users could focus on discussions centered around the main Harry/Hermione and any minor ships such
              as Lily/James and discuss canon/headcanons etc, a subsection dedicated to fanfiction whether it be finding specific fanficton, recommendations,
              discussing your favorites, or writing your own and discussing with other readers/writers, a subsection dedicated to general talk regarding the
              Harry Potter fandom that does not relate to the Harry/Hermione pairing, and a subsection for offtopic conversation where users can discuss personal
              or miscellaneous subjects.<br><br>
              Unforunately, due to unforseen technical difficulties and lack of knowhow, not everything has worked. The site is what it is, it has it's own identity now.<br><br>
              Hopefully, even if one person finds joy from it, or looks at it through rose-coloured glasses, it will have been all worth it.<br>
              Additionally, once you have had a look around, and if by chance you like what you see, or if you have some suggestions as to what could be done better, feel free to leave a comment here: <a href="/feedback"><u>Feedback</u></a>.<br>
          </p>
    </div>

    <div class="col-sm-4 my-3">
        <img src="../images/aboutpage/about.jpg" class="img-fluid w-100">
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

